The Luftwaffe (air force), Kriegsmarine (navy), and Heer (army) were the three branches of the Wehrmacht.The 'M' marked Kriegsmarine and 'L' marked Luftwaffe rifles are more sought after and generally in better condition than their 'H' marked Heer counterparts.More info on the factory rebarreling: the markings indicate that the raw forging was made by Ruhrstal, who sold it to Geco, who in turn sold the barrel to a Luftwaffe ordinance which put it into use. The barrel was made in 1940 but the rifle could have been rebarreled any time between then and the end of the war. This is a time period accurate restoration.
